  "chapter": {
    "number": 3,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Job Laments His Birth"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "After this, Job opened his mouth and cursed the day of his birth."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "And this is what he said:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“May the day of my birth perish,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the night it was said,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "‘A boy is conceived.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If only that day had turned to darkness!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "May God above disregard it;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "may no light shine upon it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "May darkness and gloom reclaim it,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a cloud settle over it;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "may the blackness of the day overwhelm it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "If only darkness had taken that night away!",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "May it not appear among the days of the year;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "may it never be entered in any of the months.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Behold, may that night be barren;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "may no joyful voice come into it.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "May it be cursed by those who curse the day",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3151
          },
          {
            "text": "—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "those prepared to rouse Leviathan.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "May its morning stars grow dark;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "may it wait in vain for daylight;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "may it not see the breaking of dawn.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For that night did not shut the doors of the womb",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to hide the sorrow from my eyes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why did I not perish at birth;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "why did I not die as I came from the womb?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why were there knees to receive me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and breasts that I should be nursed?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For now I would be lying down in peace;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I would be asleep and at rest",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "with kings and counselors of the earth,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who built for themselves cities now in ruins,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "or with princes who had gold,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who filled their houses with silver.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Or why was I not hidden like a stillborn child,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like an infant who never sees daylight?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "There the wicked cease from raging,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and there the weary find rest.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The captives enjoy their ease;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they do not hear the voice of the oppressor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Both small and great are there,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the slave is freed from his master.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why is light given to the miserable,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and life to the bitter of soul,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who long for death that does not come,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and search for it like hidden treasure,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "who rejoice and greatly exult",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when they can find the grave?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Why is life given to a man whose way is hidden,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "whom God has hedged in?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I sigh when food is put before me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and my groans pour out like water.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the thing I feared has overtaken me,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and what I dreaded has befallen me.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I am not at ease or quiet;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I have no rest, for trouble has come.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 3151,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or curse the sea",
